  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mitigating Local Conflict and Supporting Community Protection Systems in Sinjar and Ba&apos;aj</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Six years after the Islamic State (IS) carried out atrocities against the Yazidi population in Sinjar district and three years after IS was driven out of neighbouring Ba&#x2019;aj district, communities in both areas of Iraq&#x2019;s Ninewa governate face widespread insecurity as a result of inter and intra- communal conflict, militarization and lack of trust between state duty bearers in civilian population. With the Government of Iraq&#x2019;s (GoI) ongoing efforts to close IDP camps in Ninewa by early 2021, returns to both districts are likely to accelerate quickly, potentially further exacerbating risks to communities in both districts.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the project to is to improve the safety and security of target communities in Sinjar and Ba&#x2019;aj district who are vulnerable to violence.</narrative>
  </description>
